description: Commands to manage auto upgrade profiles.

commands.name: az fleet autoupgradeprofile create
commands.summary: Creates or updates an auto upgrade profile.
commands.syntax:
az fleet autoupgradeprofile create --channel {NodeImage, Rapid, Stable}
                                   --fleet-name
                                   --name
                                   --resource-group
                                   [--disabled]
                                   [--no-wait]
                                   [--node-image-selection {Consistent, Latest}]
                                   [--update-strategy-id]
examples: az fleet autoupgradeprofile create -g MyFleetResourceGroup -f MyFleetName -n MyAutoUpgradeProfileName -c Rapid --disabled
az fleet autoupgradeprofile create -g MyFleetResourceGroup -f MyFleetName -n MyAutoUpgradeProfileName -c NodeImage

commands.name: az fleet autoupgradeprofile delete
examples: az fleet autoupgradeprofile delete -g MyFleetResourceGroup -f MyFleetName -n MyAutoUpgradeProfileName

commands.name: az fleet autoupgradeprofile list
commands.summary: Lists all auto upgrade profiles for a given fleet.
examples: az fleet autoupgradeprofile list -g MyFleetResourceGroup -f MyFleetName

commands.name: az fleet autoupgradeprofile show
examples: az fleet autoupgradeprofile show -g MyFleetResourceGroup -f MyFleetName -n MyAutoUpgradeProfileName

commands.name: az fleet autoupgradeprofile wait
commands.summary: Wait for an auto upgrade resource to reach a desired state.
